<HEADLINE>
Taiwan presents silver plates to rescued Chilean miners
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei, Oct. 15 (CNA)
10/15/10  20:30:51
(By Hsieh Chia-chen and Sofia Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taiwan has presented congratulatory letters and silver-coated plates to 33
rescued Chilean miners for their bravery and ingenuity while trapped in a
collapsed mine in northern Chile, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MOFA) said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan's representative office in Chile has also conveyed the warmest wishes of
the government and people and their admiration for the remarkable rescue effort
to Chilean Foreign Minister Alfredo Moreno, the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The representative office said in its letter to Moreno that Chile's government
should be recognized and congratulated for the professional, compassionate and
efficient manner in which it handled the unprecedentedly complex rescue under
the leadership of President Sebastian Pinera.
</P>
<P>
The miners' ordeal of surviving  being trapped 624 meters underground for 69
days was an inspirational feat of endurance and resilience and a triumph of the
human spirit, the letter said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ministry said the congratulatory letters and gifts for the 33
miners were forwarded through a proper Chilean channel.
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
